  "market_context": "Daily chart showed bearish trend with a bearish order block near resistance at ~158500; 4H confirmed smooth downtrend with lower highs/lows; 1H initially bullish with a bullish order block, then broke below it.",
  "key_observation": "Price broke and closed below the 1H bullish order block (~152.200–153.500), signaling supply takeover and aligning with HTF bearish structure, triggering a short entry opportunity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identified a bearish FVG and marked the responsible candle as a bearish order block near resistance at ~158500.",
    "Step 2: On the 4H chart, confirmed bearish market structure with lower highs and lower lows, establishing a clear downtrend and marking key support at ~151500.",
    "Step 3: On the 1H chart, observed a recent bullish impulse creating a bullish order block (~152.200–153.500), which was then broken downward with a close below the zone.",
    "Step 4: Interpreted the 1H break below the bullish order block as supply taking control, validating a short entry aligned with HTF bias.",
    "Step 5: Defined entry as sell limit at new bearish order blocks, stop loss above the broken 1H order block, and target at key HTF support levels."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Top-down multi-timeframe analysis is essential: HTF defines bias and key zones, LTF provides precise entry via break of structure on order blocks; patience for high-quality setups improves trade quality.",
